<div id="c4">
<p>I have no idea what to think of Gorbachev.</p>

<p>As I see it, the main difference between Soviet Communism and the Communism practiced by China and Vietnam is that the Soviets believed in a global revolution and believed they could jump from a third world state to first world in one generation.</p>

<p>China and Vietnam seem to have no pretensions of a global revolution, and seem to see communism as the quickest way to move from third world to first world, but being realistic about its speed.</p>

<p>Practicality triumphs.</p>

<p>I don&#8217;t see that Gorbachev had much choice.  Controlling the Soviet satellite states consumed resources Russia could not afford, easing back control was tried, but ethnic loyalties exploded free the very first moment restraining force was slightly eased.</p>

